article.headline: Brown 66, Wagner 61
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Mark McAndrew scored 20 points and keyed a game-ending run that carried Brown to a 66-61 victory over Wagner on Tuesday night. The Bears (2-5) trailed 61-59 in the final minute before scoring the last seven points of the game -- five by McAndrew. His basket tied the score with 25 seconds left, and his three-point play with 9 seconds to go put Brown ahead for good. Keenan Jeppesen added two free throws with 2 seconds remaining for the final margin. Jeppesen finished with 14 points. James Ulrich led the Seahawks (1-5) with 19 points, and Mark Porter had 16. Brown went on a 23-11 run to go up 52-40 on two free throws by McAndrew with 6:58 left. Wagner took its last lead, 61-59, on a jumper by Porter. Ulrich scored eight points as Wagner jumped out to an 11-6 advantage. Brown went on a 9-0 spurt to take a 22-17 lead with 7:30 to go in the first half. The Bears led 30-27 at halftime.
